Peru Stocks: Credicorp, El Brocal, Minsur, Scotiabank Peru

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-20T21:24:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/peru-stocks-credicorp-el-brocal-minsur-scotiabank-peru.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 1 percent to 22,176.12. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1 percent to 2,791.69.  Banking shares gained after Peru’s banking association
reported total lending jumped 21 percent in June.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the local unit of
 Canada ’s third-largest bank, climbed 3.7 percent to 56 soles.
 Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, rose 2.7 percent to $96.80.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1) 
(CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA, gained 2.3 percent to 6.60 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), Peru’s largest tin producer,
advanced for a fourth session, adding 1.8 percent to 3.98 soles
after futures advanced in  London , said Estefany Castillo, an
analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
silver producer, jumped 10 percent to 47.49 soles after
announcing second-quarter net income more than doubled to $18.8
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
